## I. PROGRAM OVERVIEW

### Position Purpose

The Behavioral Support Specialist/Mentor (BSS/M) provides direct behavioral support, mentoring, and skill-building services to children and youth in foster care. This role bridges the gap between clinical intervention and daily support, offering consistent positive relationships that promote healing and growth.

### Program Philosophy

- **Relationship-First Approach:** Building trust before addressing behaviors  
- **Strength-Based Practice:** Identifying and building on existing capabilities  
- **Trauma-Informed Care:** Understanding behavior as communication  
- **Cultural Humility:** Respecting and incorporating diverse backgrounds  
- **Professional Development:** Growing future child welfare professionals
